Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/platform/riscv64/machine_code.runa" as RISCV64

Note: ============================================================================
Note: GENERIC INSTRUCTION ENCODING (Platform-Agnostic Interface)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "encode_instruction" takes opcode_id as Integer, operand_a as Integer, operand_b as Integer, operand_c as Integer, buffer_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Encode one instruction selected by abstract opcode id into buffer_ptr.
    Note: Returns encoded length in bytes, or 0 on error / unavailable op.
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 1: Return proc linux_x86_64_encode_instruction from LinuxX86_64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 2: Return proc linux_arm64_encode_instruction from LinuxARM64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 3: Return proc linux_arm32_encode_instruction from LinuxARM32 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 4: Return proc mips32_encode_instruction from MIPS32 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 5: Return proc mips64_encode_instruction from MIPS64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 6: Return proc darwin_x86_64_encode_instruction from DarwinX86_64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 7: Return proc darwin_arm64_encode_instruction from DarwinARM64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 8: Return proc freebsd_x64_encode_instruction from FreeBSDX64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 9: Return proc freebsd_arm64_encode_instruction from FreeBSDARM64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 10: Return proc netbsd_x64_encode_instruction from NetBSDX64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 11: Return proc netbsd_arm64_encode_instruction from NetBSDARM64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 12: Return proc openbsd_x64_encode_instruction from OpenBSDX64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 13: Return proc openbsd_arm64_encode_instruction from OpenBSDARM64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 14: Return proc windows_x86_64_encode_instruction from WindowsX86_64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 15: Return proc windows_arm64_encode_instruction from WindowsARM64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 16: Return proc powerpc_encode_instruction from PowerPC with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 17: Return proc riscv32_encode_instruction from RISCV32 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    If __TARGET_PLATFORM_INDEX__ is equal to 18: Return proc riscv64_encode_instruction from RISCV64 with opcode_id, operand_a, operand_b, operand_c, buffer_ptr End If
    Return 0
End Process

